articles.author: Sakshi Venkatraman
articles.title: South Asian Americans relieved as Nikki Haley drops out GOP presidential race, but worried about Trump - NBC News
articles.description: Indian American voters, 68% of whom identify as Democrats, say Nikki Haley was not the representation they wanted.
articles.content: South Asian voters watched Nikki Haley exit the presidential race on Wednesday without much fanfare. Many said they felt uninspired by Haley, who they said had a flimsy connection to the Indian Ameri… [+5795 chars]
